definition.value: Any alkylbenzene that is benzene substituted with one or more methyl groups.
A  monocyclic arene that is benzene substituted with one or more alkyl groups.
A Good's buffer substance, pKa = 6.15 at 20 degreeC.

Any member of a collection of zwitterionic buffer substances selected or devised for suitability in experimental biological systems according to a number of predetermined criteria. Named after Dr. Norman Good.
A Good's buffer substance, pKa = 8.15 at 20 degreeC.
An oxygen molecular entity that acts as an excellent buffer for many biological systems at near-neutral pH.
A member of the class of MOPS that is morpholine substituted by a 3-sulfonatopropyl group at the nitrogen atom.
Any sulfur oxoacid derivative derived from sulfurous acid.
Any magnesium ion that is positively charged.
A member of the class of oxopentanoates that is the conjugate base of 4-oxopentanoic acid.
Any chlorocycloalkane that is cyclohexane substituted by at least one chlorine group.
A chlorohydrocarbon that is any cycloalkane substituted by at least one chloro group.
Any polyamine that contains four amino groups.
A 20-carbon dicarboxylic acid which is a diterpenoid and natural carotenoid. Found in the crocus flower, it has been administered as an anti-fatigue dietary supplement.
Any  organonitrogen heterocyclic compound based on a phenazine skeleton and derivatives.
A family of macrolide natural products produced by the soil microorganism Saccharopolyspora spinosa.

A two-component mixture comprising spinosyn A and spinosyn D in a ratio of approximately 5:1. Obtained from the fermentation of the naturally occurring soil dwelling bacterium Saccharopolyspora spinosa, it is used for the topical treatment of head lice.
Mixture of 80% avermectin B1a and 20% avermectin B1b.
Mixture of 70% of milbemycin A4 and 30% of milbemycin A3.
Compounds consisting wholly of chlorine and carbon.
A member of the class of chloroethanes that is ethane in which all the hydrogens are replaced by chloro groups.
A mixture of emamectin B1a (major component) and emamectin B1b (minor component).
